10 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the stricken title, enacting clause, and
entire bill and insert:
11
12 "An Act relating to motor vehicles; amending 47 O.S.
2021, Section 7-602, as amended by Section 88,
13 Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
7-602), which relates to certification of existence
14 of security; authorizing licensed operators
discretion to accept certain form of insurance as
15 valid; and providing an effective date.
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 7-602, as
21 amended by Section 88, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
22 Section 7-602), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 7-602. A. 1. The owner of a motor vehicle registered
24 in this state shall carry in the vehicle at all times a current
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 122 Page 1

1 owne r's security verification form listing the vehicle or an
2 equivalent form which has been issued by the Department of Public
3 Safety, and the operator of the vehicle shall produce the form upon
4 request for inspection by any law enforcement officer or
5 representative of the Department and, in case of an accident, the
6 form shall be shown upon request to any person affected by the
7 accident.
8 2. a. Every person registering a motor vehicle in this
9 state, except a motor vehicle which is not being used
10 upon the public highways or public streets, or a
11 manufactured home while on a permanent foundation, at
12 the time of registration of the vehicle, shall certify
13 the existence of security with respect to the vehicle
14 by providing to a licensed operator or other
15 registering agency necessary information from the
16 current owner's security verification in a manner that
17 allows verification of coverage through the online
18 verification system. The information shall include
19 the name or number issued by the National Association
20 of Insurance Commissioners of the current insurance
21 carrier authorized to do business in this state and
22 the policy number applicable to the vehicle being
23 registered. A licensed operator or other registering
24 agency shall require the submission of the form or
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 122 Page 2

1 other verifying information prior to processing an
2 application for registration or renewal.
3 b. Every licensed operator or other registering agency
4 shall use the online verification system to certify
5 the existence of security with respect to the vehicle
6 from an insurance carrier authorized to do business in
7 this state unless the online verification system is
8 not online or the required information is otherwise
9 not available, or the licensed operator determines, in
10 the exercise of reasonable discretion, that a physical
11 proof of insurance presented by the customer appears
12 valid and sufficient to demonstrate the existence of
13 the required security. In such a case, the licensed
14 operator or other registering agency may accept
15 verification as provided in subparagraph a of this
16 paragraph, physical proof of insurance presented by
17 the customer, or from a licensed insurance producer or
18 customer service representative to certify the
19 existence of the required insurance prior to
20 processing any application for motor vehicle
21 registration. Every licensed operator or other
22 registering agent shall allow submission of proof from
23 a licensed insurance producer or customer service
24 representative pursuant to this subparagraph via
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 122 Page 3

1 electronic mail at no additional cost to the person
2 registering the vehicle.
3 3. Fleet vehicles operating under the authority of the
4 Corporation Commission, the Federal Highway Administration, or
5 vehicles registered pursuant to the provisions of Section 1120 of
6 this title, shall certify the existence of security with respect to
7 each vehicle at the time of registration by submitting one of the
8 following:
9 a. a current owner's security verification form verifying
10 the existence of security as required by the
11 Compulsory Insurance Law, or
12 b. a permit number verified by the Corporation Commission
13 indicating the existence of a current liability
14 insurance policy. Provided, in the event the
15 Corporation Commission is unable to verify the
16 existence of insurance as provided herein in a prompt
17 and timely fashion, the Corporation Commission may
18 accept a current single state registration form issued
19 by the Corporation Commission or any other regulating
20 entity with which the Corporation Commission has
21 entered into a reciprocal compact or agreement
22 regarding the regulation of motor vehicles engaged in
23 interstate or foreign commerce upon and over the
24 public highways.
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 122 Page 4

1 4. The following shall not be required to carry an owner's or
2 operator's security verification form or an equivalent form from the
3 Department of Public Safety during operation of the vehicle and
4 shall not be required to surrender a security verification form for
5 vehicle registration purposes:
6 a. any vehicle owned or leased by the federal or state
7 government, or any agency or political subdivision
8 thereof,
9 b. any vehicle bearing the name, symbol, or logo of a
10 business, corporation or utility on the exterior and
11 which is in compliance with the provisions of the
12 Compulsory Insurance Law according to records of the
13 Corporation Commission which reflect a deposit or
14 fleet policy,
15 c. fleet vehicles maintaining current vehicle liability
16 insurance as required by the Corporation Commission or
17 any other regulating entity,
18 d. any licensed taxicab, and
19 e. any vehicle owned by a licensed used motor vehicle
20 dealer.
21 5. Any person who knowingly issues or promulgates false or
22 fraudulent information in connection with either an owner's or
23 operator's security verification form or an equivalent form which
24 has been issued by the Department of Public Safety shall be guilty
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 122 Page 5

1 of a misdemeanor and upon conviction shall be subject to a fine not
2 exceeding Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or imprisonment for not
3 more than six (6) months, or by both such fine and imprisonment.
4 B. Each licensed operator is authorized to charge a fee of One
5 Dollar and fifty cents ($1.50) to each person to whom the licensed
6 operator issues a certificate of registration and who is required to
7 surrender proof of financial responsibility, or for whom the
8 licensed operator certifies the existence of financial
9 responsibility through an authorized online certification system,
10 pursuant to the provisions of the Compulsory Insurance Law. The fee
11 may be retained by the licensed operator as compensation for
12 services in processing the proof of financial responsibility and for
13 processing the driver license information, insurance verification
14 information, and other additional information furnished to the
15 licensed operator pursuant to Section 1112 of this title, if such
16 licensed operator does not receive the maximum compensation as
17 authorized by law.
18 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026."
